properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.Comment: Access: Either from Bridle Path Road or Port Hills Road, Heathcote Valley
properties.Description: The track starts with a heart pumping uphill ride to the Summit Road before descending into Lyttelton. Descent is smooth and fast with scattered humps along the way.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.RouteWarning: On road be aware of traffic
properties.Comment: Access: Either from Bridle Path Road or Port Hills Road, Heathcote Valley
properties.Description: The track starts with a heart pumping uphill ride to the Summit Road before descending into Lyttelton. Descent is smooth and fast with scattered humps along the way.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.Comment: Access: Either from Bridle Path Road or Port Hills Road, Heathcote Valley
properties.Description: The track starts with a heart pumping uphill ride to the Summit Road before descending into Lyttelton. Descent is smooth and fast with scattered humps along the way.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.Comment: Access: Head up Mt Pleasant Road to Summit Road. Alternatively bike up the Bridle Path Track.
properties.Description: Begin at the top of Castle Rock Scenic Reserve and head along a single track traversing east below Summit Road. The track switches back on itself a few times before a final traverse to the top of the Bridle Path and Summit Road.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.Comment: Access: Park at the bottom of the hill and bike up Evans Pass Road, turning right on the Summit Road.
properties.Description: Begin at the intersection of Evans Pass and Summit Roads and find the signposted track on the right about 50 m up Summit Road. The single track is smooth and well worn, watch out for large bluff drops in the middle section. Follow the track and signage and descend. Exit the playground at the end of Lower Sumnervale Reserve.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.RouteWarning: This track often closes in wet weather
properties.Comment: Access: Either Halswell Quarry car park or from Kennedys Bush Track.
properties.Description: Enter the track from the Halswell Quarry car park and weave and climb through the pine forest. Descend into a gully and climb to the start of the Kennedys Bush Track. The downhill section is great fun with many bermed corners and grade reversals.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.RouteWarning: Do not ride this track uphill
properties.Comment: Access: Park at Sign of the Kiwi and bike 2 km south-west along the Summit Road before turning right on Worsleys Road.
properties.Description: The track starts from the top of Worsleys Road climbs 400m before a right turn signals the beginning of the Flying Nun. There are some bedrock sections with wooden platforms that require slower speed along with alternate routes for the more daring with high bermed corners and jumps scattered throughout.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.RouteWarning: On road be aware of traffic
properties.Comment: Access: Leave your car in Sumner and bike up Evans Pass Road, or drive up and park.
properties.Description: The track starts past the first cattle stop on Godley Head Road. Climb through old lava flows before the track narrows and finally finishes in the Godley Head car park.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.Comment: Access: In a car park 200 m from the top of Mt Pleasant Road.
properties.Description: The first section is on a single track with some technical rocky sections. Descend gradually to Evans Pass to join the Godley Head Track on the other side of Evans Pass on Godley Head Road.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 2, easy: Mostly flat with some gentle climbs and easily avoidable obstacles.
properties.Comment: Access: From either the end of Huntsbury Ave, at the top from the Summit Road or The Bowenvale Traverse track.
properties.Description: The first section is earth surfaced but after this the track is gravel and offers a pleasant climb through open tussock country.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 2, easy: Mostly flat with some gentle climbs and easily avoidable obstacles.
properties.RouteWarning: Watch for traffic at track crossings
properties.Comment: Access: Head up Mt Pleasant Road to Summit Road or bike up the Bridle Path track.
properties.Description: The track starts before the cattle stop off to the right of Summit Road. The narrow single track traverses the top of John Britten Reserve.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.Comment: Access: Climb up Crocodile track or from Kennedys Bush Road.
properties.Description: A long ascent up the Port Hills. Riding isn't recommended during lambing season August and September

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.Comment: Access:  From Godley Head Road, travel about 4.5 km to Breezes Col.
properties.Description: A well formed track with smooth berms for cornering at speed as well as twisting sections that require concentration.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.Comment: Access:  From Godley Head Road, travel about 4.5 km to Breezes Col.
properties.Description: A well formed track with smooth berms for cornering at speed as well as twisting sections that require concentration.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.Comment: Access: Ride the Bowenvale Traverse Track to the top of the Huntsbury Track, turn off at the old airstrip after 500 m.
properties.Description: The downhill is a rough, steep, narrow gravel 4WD track heading down the valley. At the end, it's a short ride to Bowenvale Avenue.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 4, advanced: Narrow tracks, steep ascents and descents, some obstacles and exposure.
properties.Comment: Access: Ride from Victoria Park car park along the Bowenvale Traverse or along the Traverse for approx 500m towards Victoria Park from the Mt Vernon end.
properties.Description: The track begins 100 m past the first cattle stop and heads along a narrow boulder strewn track and through tussock land - great views on offer. Finish with a steep descent into Bowenvale Valley.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 2, easy: Mostly flat with some gentle climbs and easily avoidable obstacles.
properties.Comment: Access: From Cavendish Saddle at the layby beside Summit Road, follow the red capped markers to a walkover stile.
properties.Description: Climb uphill through tussock slopes and gravel road. Cross a stile and follow the route down to another stile that enters Greenwood Park. Turn left and take the Greenwood track down to Evans Pass.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.Comment: Access: Drive or ride 6.5 km from the Sign of the Kiwi east along Summit Road until you reach Mt Vernon car park.
properties.Description: The track begins with a short rocky section that levels out as it traverses beneath Mt Vernon. There is a bail out section onto Summit Road halfwayinto the ride. The second half has a few rocks and descends on smooth, well formed track to the finish.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 4, advanced: Narrow tracks, steep ascents and descents, some obstacles and exposure.
properties.Comment: Access: End of Hillsborough Terrace or Summit Road.
properties.Description: This track climbs steadily from the end of Hillsborough Terrace, the first section is steep and rutted. The track continues to climb on grass until it reaches Summit Road.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 2, easy: Mostly flat with some gentle climbs and easily avoidable obstacles.
properties.Comment: Access: Park on Centaurus Road or Vernon Terrace.
properties.Description: Ride up Rapaki Road to the start of the gravel section. Go through the gate and climb past Montgomery Spur Reserve to Summit Road.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.Comment: Access: Cycle up the Rapaki Track or access from Summit Road.
properties.Description: Climb 70 m up a smooth shared use track to the beginning of the main mountain bike track. The track makes its way around Rapaki Rock and Witch Hill.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.Comment: Access: Park on Worsley's Road and climb 2.6km up the rutted 4WD track to the car park.
properties.Description: Bike 2.1 KM and follow the signage to a single 4WD track that swoops down to join the old Dyers Pass Track.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.Comment: Access: End of Bowenvale Ave.
properties.Description: Climb 2 km up a steep 4WD track to Victoria Park and continue another 800 m to where the Bowenvale Traverse begins near Summit Road. Follow this for 2.5 km to the top of the Huntsbury Track. Follow this for 500 m before turning off by the old airstrip and joining the Bowenvale Downhill. At the end, pass a pylon and join a narrow track that will end at Bowenvale Ave.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 2, easy: Mostly flat with some gentle climbs and easily avoidable obstacles.
properties.Comment: Access: Thompsons car park at the top of Victoria Park.
properties.Description: Begin in Thompsons car park off Summit Road and turn right onto smooth gravel track. Head through pine forest and tussock country before finishing at the top of Huntsbury Track at the base of Mt Vernon.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.Comment: Access: Kennedys Bush Road
properties.Description: Climb the Kennedys Bush Track before turning onto Summit Road and continuing for 1.6 KM. Turn left up a short section of road to the top of Worsleys Spur. Descend 2.6 KM down the heavily rutted Worsley Track to Worsleys Road.

properties.MountainBikeClassification: Grade 3 terrain, intermediate: Steep slopes, rougher sections and some narrow tracks.
properties.Comment: Access: Ride the Bowenvale Traverse Track to the top of the Huntsbury Track, turn off at the old airstrip after 500 m.
properties.Description: The downhill is a rough, steep, narrow gravel 4WD track heading down the valley. At the end, it's a short ride to Bowenvale Avenue.
